{"body":"_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_

**Prevent duplicate BYOK input listeners on SPA re-entry.**

`setupBYOKEventListeners()` is meant to be re-callable, but the input listeners are added repeatedly without cleanup/guards, which can cause multiple `saveSettings()` calls per blur/Enter over time. Add a one-time guard (or remove existing listeners) similar to the toggle/clear buttons.



<details>
<summary>🧼 Suggested guard</summary>

```diff
   inputs.forEach(({ id }) => {
     const input = document.getElementById(id);
     if (input) {
+      if (input.dataset.byokListenersAttached === 'true') {
+        return;
+      }
+      input.dataset.byokListenersAttached = 'true';
       let valueBeforeEdit = '';
       input.addEventListener('focus', () => {
         valueBeforeEdit = input.value;
       });
```

</details>

As per coding guidelines, “For event listeners in JavaScript, use specific selectors and avoid broad global listeners that could interfere with existing functionality. Always include proper cleanup for listener removal.”

