{"body":"### Stale explicit cache reused across API keys

**Medium Severity**

<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->
When cached Gemini calls fail with `PERMISSION_DENIED`, the code retries without cache but keeps the old `cache_name` in `CampaignCacheManager`. After BYOK added `user_api_key`, cache ownership can differ per key, so stale cache references keep being retried on future requests, causing repeated failed cache calls in `mvp_site/llm_service.py`.
<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->

